This paper deals with the design of a secure communication system using an unmanned aerial vehicle (UAV). It involves optimizing the trajectory and resource allocation to maximize the system's confidential data rate while considering the potential presence of an eavesdropper. This problem is related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), cryptography (cs.CR), control systems (cs.SY), and robotics (cs.RO).
